title: North American invasion of Spotted-Wing Drosophila (Drosophila suzukii): A mechanistic model of population dynamics
excerpt: Temperature-based fruit fly population modelling; work from when I was a research assistant in undergrad (I did the math).
citation: Langille, Aaron B., Ellen M. Arteca, Geraldine D. Ryan, Lisa M. Emiljanowicz, and Jonathan A. Newman. "North American invasion of Spotted-Wing Drosophila (Drosophila suzukii): a mechanistic model of population dynamics."" Ecological modelling 336 (2016): 70-81.

title: The impacts of climate change on the abundance and distribution of the Spotted Wing Drosophila (Drosophila suzukii) in the United States and Canada
excerpt: An application of the fruit fly population model, running it over various predicted temperature models to observe how the populations would respond to climate change.
citation: Langille, Aaron B., Ellen M. Arteca, and Jonathan A. Newman. "The impacts of climate change on the abundance and distribution of the Spotted Wing Drosophila (Drosophila suzukii) in the United States and Canada." PeerJ 5 (2017): e3192.

title: The VM Already Knew That: Leveraging Compile-Time Knowledge to Optimize Gradual Typing
excerpt: Taking advantage of existing VM typechecks to minimize runtime typechecks, resulting in a more performant gradually typed JavaScript.
citation: Richards, Gregor, Ellen Arteca, and Alexi Turcotte. "The VM already knew that: Leveraging compile-time knowledge to optimize gradual typing." Proceedings of the ACM on Programming Languages 1, no. OOPSLA (2017): 55.

title: Reasoning About Foreign Function Interfaces Without Modelling the Foreign Languages
excerpt: Introducing nondeterministic semantics to allow us some metatheory in a well typed language with a foreign function interface, without requiring the full semantics of the foreign language.
citation: Turcotte, Alexi, Ellen Arteca, and Gregor Richards. "Learning How to Listen: Automatically FindingBug Patterns in Event-Driven JavaScript APIs." In 33rd European Conference on Object-Oriented Programming (ECOOP 2019). Schloss Dagstuhl-Leibniz-Zentrum fuer Informatik, 2019.

title: Learning How to Listen: Automatically FindingBug Patterns in Event-Driven JavaScript APIs.
excerpt: Large-scale static analysis of JavaScript code and development of statistical model to automatically determine dead event listener registrations in clients of popular event-driven APIs.
citation: Arteca, Ellen, Max Schäfer, and Frank Tip.
url_slug: Reducing Over-Synchronization in JavaScript Applications. ACM Transactions on Software Engineeringand Methodology (TOSEM).

title: Reducing Over-Synchronization in JavaScript Applications
excerpt: Static side-effect analysis to identify independent asynchronous computations, and refactoring to reorder these statements and enable concurrent execution.
citation: Arteca, Ellen, Frank Tip, and Max Schäfer. "Reducing Over-Synchronization in JavaScript Applications." In submission to 35th European Conference on Object-Oriented Programming (ECOOP 2021).
